content.text:
Tag fighters are hard and scary. I have to learn 3 whole characters before I even hit play? That sounds like work!
Dragon Ball FighterZ made the genre accessible with features that ended up influencing every fighting game that came afterwards:
- Auto Combos: mashing a button would have the character perform a simple combo, so you could just jump in and play;
- Super Dash: one button and you fly straight at your opponent. Easy to punish if you're ready for it though;
- All quarter circles: not quite the easy inputs we've seen a few games try out, but all specials and supers are done with the simplest of fighting game motions.

Paired with its incredible visual fidelity, Dragon Ball FighterZ is a game where cool stuff happens all the time regardless of your skill level. Ultimately, these things made it so even casual Dragon Ball fans would feel compelled to learn and improve at a fighting game for the first time in their lives.
